    {
      "para_id": "p7",
      "section_id": "s2",
      "section_path": [
        "Response to the Call for Evidence on the Digital Fairness Act"
      ],
      "ordinal": 7,
      "text": "The future Digital Fairness Act (DFA) needs to be established and implemented in full complementarity with existing legislation, including the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR).",
      "char_len": 185,
      "chunk_word_count": 25,
      "ratios": {
        "alpha": 0.9627329192546584,
        "digit": 0.0,
        "non_space": 0.8702702702702703
      },
      "meaning": {
        "score": 0.620660800552105,
        "flags": []
      },
      "selection": {
        "selected": true,
        "policy": "threshold+top_k"
      },
      "chunk_quality": "ok"
    },
    {
      "para_id": "p8",
      "section_id": "s2",
      "section_path": [
        "Response to the Call for Evidence on the Digital Fairness Act"
      ],
      "ordinal": 8,
      "text": "The main interactions between the GDPR and the DFA primarily involve overlapping concepts (with different meaning), and the subject matter related to digital design, profiling, and the protection of vulnerable groups, specifically children. But they are driven by distinct objectives: data protection (GDPR) versus consumer commercial fairness (DFA).",
      "char_len": 350,
      "chunk_word_count": 48,
      "ratios": {
        "alpha": 0.9570957095709571,
        "digit": 0.0,
        "non_space": 0.8657142857142858
      },
      "meaning": {
        "score": 0.9678217821782179,
        "flags": []
      },
      "selection": {
        "selected": true,
        "policy": "threshold+top_k"
      },
      "chunk_quality": "ok"
    },
    {
      "para_id": "p9",
      "section_id": "s3",
      "section_path": [
        "1. The distinct meaning of \"fairness\""
      ],
      "ordinal": 9,
      "text": "First, we recommend to explicitly clarify that the concepts of fairness within the two regulatory pieces serve different, though related, objectives:",
      "char_len": 149,
      "chunk_word_count": 21,
      "ratios": {
        "alpha": 0.9689922480620154,
        "digit": 0.0,
        "non_space": 0.8657718120805369
      },
      "meaning": {
        "score": 0.5642441860465116,
        "flags": []
      },
      "selection": {
        "selected": true,
        "policy": "threshold+top_k"
      },
      "chunk_quality": "ok"
    },
    {
      "para_id": "p10",
      "section_id": "s3",
      "section_path": [
        "1. The distinct meaning of \"fairness\""
      ],
      "ordinal": 10,
      "text": "| Regulation | Concept of Fairness/Focus | Scope | | --- | --- | --- | | GDPR | Fairness is an overarching principle for data processing: the processing of personal data must be fair. This means data should not be processed in a manner that is unlawfully discriminatory, unexpected, misleading, or unjustifiably harmful to the data subject. | Data subjects: Protection of fundamental rights regarding the processing of personal data. | | DFA | Fairness targets commercial practices in this case, these practices should not undermine choice and result in consumer detriment (e.g., financial loss, time loss, adverse health effects). | Consumers: Protection of economic interests, digital consumer protection expanded to address adverse health effects and time loss from specific harmful commercial practices. |",
      "char_len": 809,
      "chunk_word_count": 108,
      "ratios": {
        "alpha": 0.9328467153284672,
        "digit": 0.0,
        "non_space": 0.8467243510506799
