    },
    {
      "para_id": "p25",
      "section_id": "s4",
      "section_path": [
        "1. The distinct meaning of \"fairness\"",
        "2. Digital design"
      ],
      "ordinal": 25,
      "text": "Regarding Recommendation 2, the DFA can leverage the scientific evidence generated by the Spanish Data Protection Authority (AEPD) on addictive design patterns by incorporating detailed prohibitions and mandatory safeguards into its framework. The AEPD's research, based on a systematic review of scientific evidence, provides a detailed taxonomy and legal analysis of addictive design, which the DFA can integrate to ensure more effective regulation than current principle-based EU consumer laws.",
      "char_len": 497,
      "chunk_word_count": 69,
      "ratios": {
