      "section_path": [
        "3. Profiling and fairness",
        "4. Protection of vulnerable groups"
      ],
      "ordinal": 45,
      "text": "consent (Article 6(1)(a)), depends on the child's age (Article 8). The processing can be lawful where the child is at least 16 years old. Member States may establish a lower age threshold, but it must never be below 13 years. If the child is below the age threshold for consent, the processing can be lawful only if and to the extent that consent is given or authorized by the holder of parental responsibility over the child. The data controller must make reasonable efforts to verify that consent is given or authorized by the holder of parental responsibility, taking into consideration available technology.",
      "char_len": 611,
      "chunk_word_count": 104,
      "ratios": {
        "alpha": 0.9509803921568627,
        "digit": 0.013725490196078431,
        "non_space": 0.8346972176759411
