    {
      "para_id": "p50",
      "section_id": "s6",
      "section_path": [
        "3. Profiling and fairness",
        "4. Protection of vulnerable groups"
      ],
      "ordinal": 50,
      "text": "As a concluding remark, the effective relationship between the GDPR and DFA relies on the coherent and strong enforcement of both regulations. Synergies from applying different rules together (DSA, DMA, AI Act, CRA and GDPR) should be used in cases of unfair digital practices targeting consumers. Achieving this requires giving clear legal certainty on the scope, content, and interaction of the laws, and enabling closer cooperation between different enforcement authorities, such as through cooperation mechanisms between Data Protection and Consumer Protection authorities.",
